comment_data.body:
It's quite unfortunate that the ordering of except vs. nogil now makes the white-space after `except +` semantically relevant. If only to mitigate that, I fully agree that `+nogil` should be forbidden.

I tried chasing down the decision for the ordering, and AFAICT, it was [made](https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4670#discussion_r854489596) directly in the PR. So, for completeness, a comparison of all possible combinations:

### Current status: first `except` qualifier, then `gil` qualifier
```
noexcept nogil:
noexcept with gil:
except <val> nogil:
except <val> with gil:
except? <val> nogil:
except? <val> with gil:
except * nogil:
except * with gil:
except + nogil:                # only separated from `except +<handler>` (without gil-qualifier) by a single space
except + with gil:
except +* nogil:
except +* with gil:
except +<PyError> nogil:
except +<PyError> with gil:
except +<handler> nogil:
except +<handler> with gil:
```

There are IMO a bunch more cases above where presumably the space before `nogil` / `with gil` should be made mandatory, even though we might parse correctly without it (like `except *nogil`).

### Parallel world: first `gil` qualifier, then `except` qualifier

```
nogil noexcept:
nogil except <val>:
nogil except? <val>:
nogil except *:
nogil except +:
nogil except +*:
nogil except +<PyError>:
nogil except +<handler>:
with gil noexcept:
with gil except <val>:
with gil except? <val>:
with gil except *:
with gil except +:
with gil except +*:
with gil except +<PyError>:
with gil except +<handler>:
```

Personally I think the second set looks better, aside from the fact that it does not suffer from any ambiguity or semantically relevant whitespace. But I also guess it's too late to change it now that we're in the beta phase already and projects have started responding to the warnings about the ordering.

@scoder @da-woods 
Seeing that this is currently one of the main blockers for 3.0 (cannot deprecate something that 0.29.x cannot even do correctly yet), can we decide how to handle this?

I'm not sure if it's worth the churn to change the order of the gil & except qualifiers to avoid the ambiguities in the first place, but if so 3.0 is the only time to do it (and I guess we could say we're not in rc phase yet). If so (and it's a big if), it should IMO be part of the next beta.
